ABSTRACT
A method and apparatus is presented for announcing the
existence of cryptographic key pairs within a distributed
ledger system in which no central trusted authority is
available, consisting of sending a key announcement mes-
sage by a network connected device to other network
connected devices over a peer-to-peer network for inclusion
in the distributed ledger. Once a valid key announcement
message for a public key is included in the ledger, any future
transactions that reference an address associated with the
public key or other messages concerning said public key are
accepted by other network connected devices on the peer-
to-peer network and are included in the distributed ledger. If
transactions or other messages reference an address not
associated with an announced public key, they may be
rejected by the peer-to-peer network and may not be
included in the distributed ledger.
